  "label": "Charterhouse Narrow Bedchamber",
  "description": "This compact upper-floor bedroom is built into the rowhouse’s blackened-brick shell, its ceiling crossed by riveted iron straps that brace the refounded masonry. A slit-window with heavy shutters admits a thin, regulated light, and its deep sill serves as a spare writing ledge. The bedstead is set beside a soot-stained hearth flue boxed in plaster, with a built-in cupboard for folded kit and sealed papers. The door is thick-planked and iron-latched, matching the lodging’s defensible, licensable character.",
